
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `gpic` baraye sakhtane diagram-ha va nemoode-ha az matn estefade mishavad. In dastoor, matn-ha ra mikhanad va ba estefade az zabane `pic`, diagram-ha ra tarrah mikonad. natije-ye kar, code PostScript ast ke mitavan an ra chap kard ya dar digar barname-ha estefade kard.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `-t`  --> 🖼️  Natije ra be jaye PostScript be format troff ersal mikonad, baraye estefade dar troff/groff.
    🔹 `-s`  --> 📐 Size-e nemoode-ha ra baraye chap beینه mikonad.
    🔹 `-w width` --> ↔️   پهنای diagram را مشخص میکند.
    🔹 `-g` --> 🐛  Debug mode ra fa'al mikonad.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ gpic file.pic > file.ps

    🔹 File `file.pic` ra be PostScript tabdil mikonad va dar `file.ps` zakhire mikonad.

    $ gpic -t file.pic | troff -ms

    🔹 File `file.pic` ra be format troff tabdil mikonad va ba `troff` process mikonad.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ gpic input.pic > output.ps

    🔹 Agar `input.pic` shamel dastoorat `pic` baraye tarrahi yek diagram bashad, in dastoor `output.ps` ra ba code PostScript baraye chap ya namayesh diagram misazad.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `gpic` command is used to create diagrams and figures from text descriptions. It reads text files containing descriptions in the `pic` language and generates diagrams.  The output is PostScript code, which can be printed or used in other programs.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `-t`  --> 🖼️  Sends the output to troff instead of PostScript, for use with troff/groff.
    🔹 `-s`  --> 📐 Optimizes figure sizes for printing.
    🔹 `-w width` --> ↔️ Specifies the width of the diagram.
    🔹 `-g` --> 🐛 Enables debug mode.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ gpic file.pic > file.ps

    🔹 Converts `file.pic` to PostScript and saves it as `file.ps`.

    $ gpic -t file.pic | troff -ms

    🔹 Converts `file.pic` to troff format and processes it with `troff`.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ gpic input.pic > output.ps

    🔹 If `input.pic` contains `pic` language instructions for drawing a diagram, this command will create `output.ps` with the PostScript code to print or display that diagram.

